topic.body:
Basically what I see is ZeroHello has that yellow buttons in left sidebar, allowing to raise the limits for each zite. It is also possible to do same operation when you're visiting that particular zite.

If I created my own zite, I can measure if any other zite is reaching the limits, by doing `Cors` + `as`:
```
// Cors request allowed first, then...
    page.cmdp("as", [ziteAddress, "siteInfo"]).then((response) => {
      let currentZiteSizeInBytes = response.settings.size;
      let sizeLimitForZiteInBytes = response.size_limit * 1000000;
      if (currentZiteSizeInBytes >= sizeLimitForZiteInBytes) {
        // Do something
      }
    });
```

But I can't figure out if I can actually set the size limit to a remote zite from my own zite? Or only ZeroHello is able to do that?..

